Introduction
This first part of the reference documentation is an overview of Spring CodeConfig and the underlying concepts.
Concepts
The goal of Spring CodeConfig is to provide an rich code configuration capability rooted in code rather than the more common XML.
Object Definitions are CodeThe simplest way to understand CodeConfig is to investigate a working sample.
Reference
This part of the reference documentation details the various components that comprise Spring CodeConfig.
